The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: Direct tax collections including corporate and personal income tax have grown 46.95 per cent to Rs 71,648 crore in April-July this year mainly because of the surge in tax deducted at source (TDS) receipts and buoyancy in corporate profits. Robust growth in direct tax collections is a result of tax education and compliance mechanism put in place by the income tax department in the area of TDS and tax collection at source, said a finance ministry statement.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority (NPPA) has revised the prices of six bulk drugs used in the manufacturing of medicines in the country. The revised notified prices shall become effective within 15 days from the date of notification, NPPA said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: The government today cleared 24 FDI proposals worth Rs 753.14 crore including Japan-based Daiichi Sankyos proposed acquisition of shares and warrants in Ranbaxy.                            
	 New York, Aug. 6: Microsoft will buy back as much as $20 billion of its stock to boost its flagging share price, Bloomberg News quoted a software analyst as saying.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 6: NHPC will be the first PSU to go for an IPO after the Lefts withdrawal of support to the UPA government as the power producer today filed a revised draft red herring prospectus with Sebi.                                                                                                                         
